        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the filling and bake the pies",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat a frying pan over a medium-high heat. Cook the onion in a little oil for 6 minutes until soft. Add the mince and brown, breaking it up. Add the stock and Worcestershire sauce. Season and simmer for 10 minutes until the liquid reduces to a thick, clingy gravy. Cool.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Line four individual small tins or one rectangular tin with two-thirds of the pastry. Fill with the cooled mince mixture. Top with the remaining pastry, press edges to seal, and brush with egg. Make a small steam hole in each pie top.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the pastry is golden and crisp. Rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the mash and liquor",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Boil the potatoes in salted water for 18 to 20 minutes until tender. Drain well and mash with the butter and warm milk until smooth. Season generously.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Bring the vegetable stock to a simmer in a medium saucepan. Whisk in the cornflour mixture and stir for 2 minutes until the sauce thickens slightly. It should be thin rather than thick. Stir in the parsley off the heat and season.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Serve a pie on each plate alongside a generous mound of mash. Pour the liquor over both generously at the table.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Liquor should pour freely. Add a splash more stock and stir to loosen.",
                "cause": "Too much cornflour or reduced too long.",
                "symptom": "The liquor is too thick"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add the parsley off the heat just before serving.",
                "cause": "Parsley added while the sauce was too hot and cooked in.",
                "symptom": "The liquor loses its bright green colour"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Reduce the filling until the liquid is almost fully absorbed before cooling and adding to the pastry.",
                "cause": "Filling was too wet when assembled.",
                "symptom": "The pastry base is soggy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a potato ricer or hand masher. Never blend or food-process potatoes for mash.",
                "cause": "Overworked or blended rather than mashed.",
                "symptom": "The mash is gluey"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Pie-and-mash shops have operated in East and South London since the Victorian era, when they fed the city's working poor with cheap, filling food. The shops are distinguished by white tiles, wooden benches, and marble counters, and the menu has barely changed in a hundred years. The liquor was originally made from the water in which live eels were boiled, but modern shops use vegetable stock. The dish remains a living piece of London working-class food history.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
